Reasoning: The paper deals with constructing linear decision trees for combinatorial and discrete geometry problems, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. The use of machine learning techniques and the mention of the VC dimension suggest that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the SUBSET-SUM problem, which is a classic problem in computational complexity, suggesting that it could belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Finally, the use of linear queries and the mention of optimal number of queries suggest that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
